  "_doc": "Curated job source list. This file seeds the `job_sources` DB table on first run. After seeding, the DB is the source of truth \u2014 edits here only take effect on the next seed run (or via the admin API). ats: greenhouse | lever | ashby | workable | smartrecruiters | workday | career_page. priority: 10=hourly, 7=every 3h, 5=twice daily, 1=daily. active=false means skip without deleting. Workable/SmartRecruiters entries below are seeded active=false \u2014 spot-check the public URL (apply.workable.com/{token}/ or jobs.smartrecruiters.com/{token}) before enabling. A failing source is graceful (0 jobs, no crash) but wastes a request; verify first. Entries below marked active=false with the note `dead_2026-07-15` are ones the spot-check confirmed returned 0 jobs against their ATS endpoint \u2014 the token is wrong, the company migrated ATS, or the company no longer publishes a public feed. Re-enable via `PATCH /admin/job-sources/{id}/toggle` after finding the correct token.",
